    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed the required level for Model Risk Level 3. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required level of 3; this gap is accepted given the standardised nature of the ASTM F1717 protocol and the availability of supplementary sensitivity analysis demonstrating robustness across load magnitudes. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-specified acceptance bounds (E/uval < 1.96, percent difference < 10%). The FEA modeling framework is assessed as sufficiently credible to support the regulatory submission claim for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct.",
